Allosaurus|15th|Animal||Huge|40 ft.|Str +7, Dex +1, Con +4, Int -4, Wis +1, Cha +0|Notice!+21!18 ranks, +1 Wis, +2 bonus|Improved Grab!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Run!,;Tough! (x3),;Track| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>|+10!(-2 size, +11 base, +1 Dex);+14!(bite);20/--!(21 base, -2 size, +1 Dex);+1|+13!+4 size, +4 Con, +2 natural, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+13!+9 base, +4 Con;+10!+9 base, +1 Dex;+6!+5 base, +1 Wis|</p><p>An allosaurus is somewhat smaller than a <a href="Creatures.php?Name=Tyrannosaurus">tyrannosaurus</a>, but is similar in form, standing on two powerful hind legs and a long tail extending out behind it for balance. These creatures are usually some 25 feet long and weigh one and a half tons. Allosauruses typically hunt in packs of up to ten individuals, chasing down their prey before delivering a killing blow with their massive jaws.|<b>Skills:</b> An allosaurus has a +2 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>:</b> Creatures up to two sizes smaller; +13 bludgeoning damage and +5 acid damage per round; gizzard Toughness save +9; an allosaurus' gizzard can hold 2 Medium, 8 Small, 32 Tiny, or 128 Diminutive or smaller opponents.|
Ancestral Guardian|11th|Spirit||Large|30 ft.|Str +7, Dex +0, Con --, Int +2, Wis +2, Cha +3|Intimidate!+17!14 ranks, +3 Cha;Knowledge (local)!+16!14 ranks, +2 Int;Notice!+16!14 ranks, +2 Wis;Sense Motive!+16!14 ranks, +2 Wis;Stealth!+12!14 ranks, +0 Dex, -2 size|Attack Focus!(<a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Maul">maul</a>),;Defensive Attack!,;Improved Disarm!,;Improved Initiative|Heavy Step, Soul Pool, Gather Soul, Soul Driven, other guardian abilities (see below)|+11!(+11 base, +0 Dex, -1 size, +1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Attack%20Focus">Attack Focus</a>);+11!(+4 <a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Maul">maul</a>, +7 Str);20/26!(+11 base, +0 Dex, -1 size/+11 base, +7 Str, -1 size);+4!(+0 Dex, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Initiative">Improved Initiative</a>)|+12!(+0 Con, +12 natural armor);+7!+7 base, +0 Con;+7!+7 base, +0 Dex;+9!+7 base, +2 Wis|Appearing as immense constructs, these impressive figures are actually spirits powered by the souls of the venerated deceased of the village or community they have been bound to protect. Different ancestral guardians appear differently, but they are all set with numerous precious-looking stones. They do not obey commands but instead act of their own accord to defend the community whose souls they bear.|<b>Heavy Step:</b> Ancestral guardians only move three times their speed when they run.</p><p><b>Soul Pool:</b> An ancestral guardian relies on the crystallized essences of the dead for its power. Each soul contributes points to a soul pool that the ancestral guardian can draw upon in order to use some of its special abilities. An encountered ancestral guardian will have a number of souls in its possession equal to one or two times its level. The maximum number of souls an ancestral guardian may posses is four times its level. Using points from the pool does not destroy the souls, but it exhausts their energy for a time. Points used return at a rate of one point per day.</p><p><b>Soul Driven:</b> An ancestral guardian's soul pool fuels not only its special abilities, but also its ability to animate itself. Should an ancestral guardian deplete its soul pool entirely, it weakens itself to a point that it can do nothing more than take a single <a href="CombatActions.php?Time=Move">move action</a> each round. This state persists until the ancestral guardian has recovered at least one point to its soul pool.</p><p><b>Gather Soul:</b> Any member of the ancestral guardian's protected community reduced to <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Dying">dying</a> within 60 feet of the ancestral guardian has its soul drawn into the guardian's soul pool. Each soul adds a number of points to the ancestral guardian's soul pool equal to the dying character's level. If these points exceed the ancestral guardian's maximum, the soul cannot be drawn into the pool.</p><p><b>Retaliatory Strike:</b> An ancestral guardian gets a +2 bonus on attack rolls against any creature that struck them in the previous round. Even an ancestral guardian that has expended its entire soul pool may make an attack against a creature that struck it last round.</p><p><b>Special Powers:</b> In addition to the abilities described above, ancestral guardians will have one or more of the following special abilities:</p><p><i>Guard:</i> As a reaction, an ancestral guardian can choose to absorb any damage dealt to an adjacent creature or object from its community. Guardians cannot block any damage that is not opposed by a Toughness save. By expending 1 point from its soul pool, the ancestral guardian takes half the damage dealt to the creature or object it is guarding, and the creature or object takes half as well. If the ancestral guardian expends 2 points from its soul pool, it takes the full damage and the guarded creature or object takes none.</p><p><i>Improved Retaliatory Strike:</i> An ancestral spirit can expend a point from its soul pool to gain an additional +2 bonus to its retaliatory strike attack, and to gain a +1 bonus on damage dealt by that attack.</p><p><i>Ancestral Wrath:</i> Some ancestral guardians may use supernatural <a href="Powers.php">powers</a>. They use these powers with power ranks equal to their level. Each power requires the listed number of points from their soul pool: <a href="Powers.php?Name=Heart%20Shaping">Heart Shaping</a> (2), <a href="Powers.php?Name=Psychic%20Blast">Psychic Blast</a> (4), <a href="Powers.php?Name=Truth%20Reading">Truth Reading</a> (2), <a href="Powers.php?Name=Ward">Ward</a> (4).|
