can cause a black bile jelly to split into two.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> *A black bile jelly gains a +16 bonus to <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks when in dark or gloomy conditions.|
Blemmyae|5th|Monstrous Humanoid||Medium|30 ft., climb 15 ft.|Str +5, Dex +2, Con +2, Int +0, Wis +1, Cha -1|Climb!+13!8 ranks, +5 Str;Jump!+13!8 ranks, +5 Str;Notice!+5!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus|All-out Attack!,;Cleave!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> to 60 feet, Scream of Rage|+7!(+5 base, +2 Dex);+7!(+2 club, +5 Str);17/20!(+5 base, +2 Dex/+5 base, +5 Str);+2|+5!+2 Con, +3 natural armor;+3!+1 base, +2 Con;+6!+4 base, +2 Dex;+5!+4 base, +1 Wis|Blemmyae are naked, club-wielding savages with no heads, and their faces in their burly chests. They stand seven to eight feet tall (at the shoulder, yuk yuk yuk) and are covered in thick, coarse hair. They live in deep jungles and protect their territory with agressive displays and will attack any creatures that do not immediately retreat.|Blemmyae only advance by taking levels of <a href="CreaturesTypes.php?Name=Monstrous%20Humanoid">monstrous humanoid</a>.</p><p><b>Scream of Rage:</b> The blemmyae have huge resonating chest cavities with which they are able to produce this horrendous noise at will. All creatures within 60 ft. must succeed at a Difficulty 14 Will save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=shaken">shaken</a> for one minute. A character who fails this save and is exposed to a second blemmyae scream of rage must, in addition to the second Will save, make a Difficulty 14 Fortitude save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Deafened">deafened</a> for one hour. These save Difficulties are Constitution-based.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Blemmyae have a +4 racial bonus to <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks.|
Brachiosaurus|15th|Animal||Gargantuan|25 ft.|Str +9, Dex +0, Con +6, Int -5, Wis -1, Cha +0|Notice!+18!19 ranks, -1 Wis|Awesome Blow!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Tough! (x5)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Trample">Trample</a>|+7!(-4 size, +11 base, +0 Dex);+16!(tail sweep);17/--!(21 base, -4 size, +0 Dex);+0|+19!+6 size, +6 Con, +2 natural, +5 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+15!+9 base, +6 Con;+9!+9 base, +0 Dex;+4!+5 base, -1 Wis|A brachiosaurus is a towering creature, 40 feet tall and weighing 30 tons. It walks on four legs, with the front legs longer than the back, much like a modern-day giraffe. These enormous herbivores swat enemies with their muscular tails.</p><p>Much like the <a href="Creatures.php?Name=Apatosaurus">apatosaurus</a>, these creatures are found both larger and smaller than listed here. This is simply a representative individual.|<b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Trample">Trample</a>:</b> Damage +23, Difficulty 26 Reflex Save for half damage. The save Difficulty is Strength- based.|
Cannibal Spirit|11th|Spirit||Medium|fly 120 ft. (perfect)|Str +6, Dex +4, Con +5, Int +3, Wis +5, Cha +7|Knowledge!(local) +17!14 ranks, +3 Int;Notice!+19!14 ranks, +5 Wis;Search!+18!14 ranks, +4 Dex;Stealth!+18!14 ranks, +4 Dex;Survival!+19!14 ranks, +5 Wis|Ability Focus! (dream haunting),;Ability Focus! (howl),;Double Strike!,;Improved Grab!,;!<a href="Powers.php">Powers</a> (<a href="Powers.php?Name=Wind%20Shaping">Wind Shaping</a>),;Track!,;Wind Finesse|Dream Haunting, Howl, No Breath, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Rake">Rake</a>|+15!(bite) (+11 base, +4 Dex) (<b>+13</b> claw);+9!(bite) or <b>+7</b> (claw) or (<b>+9</b> rake);25/--!(+11 base, +4 Dex);+8!(+4 Dex, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Initiative">Improved Initiative</a>|+5!+5 Con;+12!+7 base, +5 Con;+13!+7 base, +4 Dex, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Lightning%20Reflexes">Lightning Reflexes</a>;+12!+7 base, +5 Wis|Terrible spirits of hunger and fear, these spirits generally haunt isolated sites where hunger and deprivation drove people to fearful acts of violence. Different cannibal spirits appear in different forms but typically they possess a humanoid shape, but with revolting bestial features.|<b>Dream Haunting:</b> A cannibal spirit can visit the dreams of a single victim within 1 mile while that victim sleeps. The afflicted individual experiences vivid nightmares of starvation and cannibalism. The victim can resist the effects of this dream with a Difficulty 24 Will save. Failure indicates the victim takes a level of fatigue as they sleep, but can't quite remember the nature of their dreams. After failing two of these saves against the same cannibal spirit, the victim contracts <em>Cannibal Fever</em> (see below). A victim who saves three times against the same cannibal spirit is forever immune to that cannibal spirit's dream haunting ability. This is a mind-influencing effect. The save Difficulty is Charisma-based.</p><p><b>Howl:</b> Up to three times per day as a standard action, a cannibal spirit can let loose a forlorn howl that echoes throughout the countryside and can be heard up to a mile away &mdash; even during the fiercest storm &mdash; unless magically silenced. This primal howl raises the hackles of all who hear it and sends chills down the spine. Anyone who hears the howl must make a Difficulty 24 Will save to avoid becoming <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Shaken">shaken</a> for an hour. Creatures within 120 feet of the cannibal spirit when it howls also become <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Panicked">panicked</a> for one minute, and those within 30 feet also become <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Paralyzed">paralyzed</a> with fear for three rounds. Anyone who makes the save is immune to that cannibal spirit's howl for 24 hours. This is a mind-influencing fear effect. The save Difficulty is Charisma-based.</p><p><b>Cannibal Fever:</b> When a victim suffers a cannibal spirit's dream haunting or wind walks with one, he contracts this terrible malady. Sometimes those who practice cannibalism of their own accord also develop these symptoms.</p><p>Cannibal Fever acts as a <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Disease">disease</a>. It has an incubation period of 1 day, and inflicts a point of Wisdom damage each day the victim fails a Difficulty 22 Will save. During this time, the cannibalistic visions become more and more vivid and personal, and begin to involve family members and friends. Cannibal Fever cannot reduce a victim's Wisdom to lower than -5, but once this point is reached, the victim seeks out other humans to kill and consume.</p><p>Once a victim actually commits an act of cannibalism, a cannibal spirit takes over the victim's body, and screaming, the victim is drawn up into the air, to be transformed into a new spirit of cannibalism.|
Carrionstorm|3rd|Undead|Swarm|Tiny|10 ft., fly 40 ft. (good)|Str -5, Dex +0, Con --, Int -4, Wis +2, Cha -2|Notice!+8!6 ranks, +2 Wis|Ability Focus!(distraction);Improved Initiative|Distraction, Pallid Bond, Vulnerable to Ward|Swarm;+2;13/--!(+1 base, +0 Dex, +2 size);+4!(+0 Dex, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Initiative">Improved Initiative</a>)|-2!+0 base, -2 size;--;+1!+1 base, +0 Dex;+5!+3 base, +2 Wis|Where the dead walk, the carrion birds follow. In most cases, birds that feast on the flesh of the undead simply grow diseased and die. Yet the flesh of some ghouls has an altogether different effect on such scavengers, for when they die from the poisoned repast, they do not stay dead for long. Alone, the isolated undead crow or vulture is little more than a hideous mockery, but where ghoulish activity is thick, entire flocks of carrion birds can succumb to undeath, retaining their flock mentality but no longer seeking the flesh of the recently dead. Carrionstorms, as these flocks of undead birds are called, find brief respite from their morbid hunger only when their meals are warm and screaming.|<b>Distraction:</b> Any living creature that begins its turn with a carrionstom in its square must succeed on a Difficulty 13 Fortitude save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Nauseated">nauseated</a> for one round. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.</p><p><b>Pallid Bond:</b> A carrionstorm never attacks undead creatures.</p><p><b>Vulnerable to Warding:</b> A use of the <a href="Powers.php?Name=Ward">Ward</a> power against a carrionstorm deals damage with a bonus equal to the adept's power bonus for the attempt. The carrionstorm uses its Toughness save, not its Will save, to try and resist this damage.|
Cockroach, Giant|4th|Vermin||Large|50 ft.|Str +4, Dex +1, Con +3, Int --, Wis +1, Cha -3|Notice!+5!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus;Stealth!+5!0 ranks, +1 Dex, +4 bonus|Improved Initiative!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> (60 ft.), <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Light%20Sensitivity">Light Sensitivity</a>|+3!(+3 base, -1 size, +1 Dex);+6!(bite);13/--!(13 base, -1 size, +1 Dex);+5!(+1 Dex, +4 Imp. Init.)|+6!+3 Con, +3 chitin;+7!+4 base, +3 Con;+2!+1 base, +1 Dex;+2!+1 base, +1 Wis|These monstrous scavengers will eat almost anything, and will even attack smaller living creatures when hungry. Otherwise, giant roaches tend to be timid creatures, and often flee when confronted. In larger groups, they may be a bit more belligerent. They particularly dislike bright light and usually run away from it.|<b>Skills:</b> A giant cockroach has a +4 bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.</p><p>The cockroach's <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> bonus increases to +12 when amidst dark soil, rotting leaves or other decomposing organic matter.|
Composognathus|2nd|Animal||Small|40 ft.|Str -2, Dex +4, Con +1, Int -4, Wis +3, Cha +0|Jump!+2!0 ranks, -2 Str, +4 bonus;Notice!+12!5 ranks, +3 Wis, +4 bonus;Stealth!+8!0 ranks, +4 Dex, +4 bonus|Dodge Focus!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>|+7!(+2 size, +1 base, +4 Dex);-1!(bite);+8/--!(+2 size, +1 base, +4 Dex, +1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Dodge%20Focus">Dodge Focus</a>);+4|+1!-1 size, +1 Con, +1 natural;+4!+3 base, +1 Con;+7!+3 base, +4 Dex;+3!+0 base, +3 Wis|A compsognathus is a small, agile predator that travels in large packs and inflicts a poisonous bite on its prey, then waits for the poison to take effect. These creatures gang up on larger prey, with many pack members leaping in to bite once, then retreating. The pack then follow their victim, administering further bites if the prey does not appear to be collapsing. Once the prey is helpless the pack close in for their meal.|<b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>:</b> Bite; Fortitude Difficulty 12 resists; initial and secondary damage 1 Str. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A compsognathus has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Jump">Jump</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks.|
Crypt Wight|4th|Undead||Medium|30 ft.|Str +4, Dex +1, Con --, Int +1, Wis +2, Cha +4|Notice!+9!7 ranks, +2 Wis;Search!+8!7 ranks, +1 Int;Intimidate!+11</b> (7 ranks, +4 Cha;Stealth!+8!7 ranks, +1 Dex;Knowledge! (any) +8!7 ranks, +1 Int|Power:Cold Shaping!+11;Power:Heart Shaping!+11;Power:Sleep!+11|Burned by Sunlight, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> 60 ft.|+3!(+2 base, +1 Dex);+5!(slam, +2 cold aura);13/--!(+2 base, +1 Dex);+1|+7!+5 natural armor;--;+2!+1 base, +1 Dex;+6!+4 base, +2 Wis|Crypt wights are corpses of the ancient dead animated by malevolent spirits from another plane. Their bodies are shriveled to little more than leathery skin clinging to their bones, shrouded by tattered rags and rusting armor. They are surrounded by an aura of bitter cold, and their icy touch saps the warmth from the living. These fell beings shun sunlight, which sears their unholy flesh. Crypt wights rarely stray far from their burial mounds, and even then only at night.|<b>Burned by Sunlight:</b> A crypt wight takes +2 fire damage each round it spends in direct sunlight.|
Deathweb|9th|Undead||Gargantuan|30 ft., climb 20 ft.|Str +7, Dex +2, Con --, Int -2, Wis +1, Cha +1|Climb!+27!12 ranks, +7 Str, +8 bonus;Notice!+13!12 ranks, +1 Wis;Stealth!+2!12 ranks, +2 Dex, -12 size|All-out Attack!,;Awesome Blow!,;Cleave!,;Improved Bull Rush!,;Multi-attack|Poison Swarm, Web|+2!(+4 base, +2 Dex, -4 size);+10!+3 base, +7 Str;12/--!(+4 base, +2 Dex, -4 size);+2|+11!+0 base, +6 size, +5 natural armour;--;+5!+3 base, +2 Dex;+7!+6 base, +1 Wis|Deathwebs are the exoskeletons of truly massive monstrous arachnids animated by foul magics, and masses of smaller, symbiotic spiders. Although their bodies resemble the powerful predators they once were, they are now broken, hollow things, teeming swarms of their lesser kin. Potent necromantic energies might create most deathwebs, but these horrors have also been known o animate spontaneously in areas teeming with insectile vermin or tainted by the worship of perverse spider cults.|<b>Poison Swarm:</b> The area around a deathweb is filled with swarms of living spiders taht nest in the undead thing's exoskeleton. Any creature that comes within 10 feet of a deathweb takes +1 piercing damage per round and must make a difficulty 15 Fortitude save or be <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">poisoned</a> (initial: immediate, 1 Con; secondary: 2 minutes, 2 Con). The save Difficulty is Charisma-based.</p><p>Any <a href="CombatModifiers.php?Name=Area%20Attack">area attack</a> that deals a <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Wounded">wounded</a> result to the deathweb destroys its poison swarm for 3 rounds. After this time, new spiders well up from within the beast and create a new swarm.</p><p><b>Web:</b> The deathweb can create sticky webs to ensnare enemies. A deathweb can throw a web at will, but no more than once every 5 rounds. This is similar to an attack with a <a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Net">net</a> but has a maximum range of 50 feet, with a range increment of 10 feet, and is effective against Colossal or smaller opponents. As a standard action, an entangled creature can escape with a Difficulty 21 <a href="Skills.php?Name=Escape%20Artist">Escape Artist</a> check or burst it with a Difficulty 29 Strength check. The check Difficulties are Strength-based, and the Strength check Difficulty includes a +8 racial bonus.</p><p>The slimy webbing created by a deathweb has a Toughness save of +8. It is difficulty to burn and has <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Resistance%20to%20Energy">energy resistance</a> +5 vs fire. Fires that achieve a <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Disabled">disabled</a> result against the web destroy it; they also inflict fire damage on creatures entangled in the web.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Deathwebs have a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks. A deathweb can always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened.|
Deinonychus|4th|Animal||Large|60 ft.|Str +4, Dex +2, Con +4, Int -4, Wis +1, Cha +0|Jump!+19!7 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus, +2 speed;Notice!+9!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +8 bonus;Stealth!+6!0 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus, -2 size;Survival!+9!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +8 bonus|Double Strike!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Run!,;Track!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>|Flying Charge, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Pounce">Pounce</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+4!(-1 size, +3 base, +2 Dex);+8!(talons) or <b>+4</b> (foreclaws) or <b>+6</b> (bite);+4/--!(-1 size, +3 base, +2 Dex);+2|+8!+2 size, +4 Con, +2 natural;+8!+4 base, +4 Con;+6!+4 base, +2 Dex;+2!+1 base, +1 Wis|A deinonychus is clad in a colourful pelt of feathers, and resembles a land-bound bird with clawed arms instead of wings, and a powerful jaw full of teeth instead of a beak. Its tail extends straight out behind itself, held aloft by an intricate structure of bony supports, thus allowing its weight to be carried entirely by the back legs. It weighs about 600 pounds.</p><p>A deinonychus uses a combination of speed, grasping forearms, large teeth and hind legs with ripping talons. It hunts by running at prey, leaping, and ripping with its rear talons as it claws and bites.</p><p>The talons count as only one attack. A deinonychus has a relatively large brain for a dinosaur, and its pack hunts with cunning tactics.|<b>Flying Charge:</b> A deinonychus can use a <a href="Skills.php?Name=Jump">Jump</a> action as part of its <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Charge">charge</a> movement.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Pounce">Pounce</a>:</b> If a deinonychus <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Charge">charges</a>, it can attack a single target with both its talons and its bite in a single round.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A deinonychus has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Jump">Jump</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Survival">Survival</a> checks.|
Dimetrodon|3rd|Animal||Large|20 ft.|Str +4, Dex -1, Con +4, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha +0|Notice!+11!6 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus;Stealth!-1!0 ranks, -1 Dex|Improved Grab! (bite),;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Tough| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, Shake|+0!(-1 size, +2 base, -1 Dex);+8!(bite);+0/--!(-1 size, +2 base, -1 Dex);-1|+9!+2 size, +4 Con, +2 natural,+1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+7!+3 base, +4 Con;+2!+3 base, -1 Dex;+0!+1 base, -1 Wis|A dimetrodon is about 10 feet long and weighs 500 pounds. It is a lizard-like creature with an immense sail running the length of its back.</p><p>Dimetrodons attack from ambush when they can, leaping forward and seizing their prey in their powerful jaws.|<b>Shake:</b> If a dimetrodon successfully starts a <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Grapple">grapple</a> with its bite attack, it deals automatic bite damage each round it maintains the hold as it shakes its prey violently in its jaws. The dimetrodon can deal this damage even if moving or pinning its opponent.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A dimetrodon has a +4 bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks.|
Dragonfly, Giant|6th|Vermin||Large|25 ft., fly 80 ft. (good)|Str +2, Dex +2, Con +2, Int --, Wis +2, Cha +0|Notice!+10!0 ranks, +2 Wis, +8 bonus|Improved Initiative!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Snatch!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a>| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> 60 ft., <a href="CreaturesTypes.php?Name=Vermin">Vermin Traits</a>|+5!(-1 size, +4 base, +2 Dex);+5!(bite);+5/--!(-1 size, +4 base, +2 Dex);+6|+6!+2 size, +2 Con, +2 natural;+7!+5 base, +2 Con;+4!+2 base, +2 Dex;+4!+2 base, +2 Wis|These aerial predators are very territorial. They often attack lone predators and occasionally small caravans while in search of food, but may also become aggressive when its territory is entered by another creature that it perceives as a threat (including other giant dragonflies of the same gender). Giant dragonflies are around 14 feet in length, and weigh around 600 pounds.|<b>Skills:</b> A giant dragonfly has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.|
Eryops|5th|Animal||Huge|15 ft.|Str +5, Dex -1, Con +2, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha +0|Notice!+1!0 ranks, +1 Wis;Stealth!+10!8 ranks, -1 Dex, -8 size, +8 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>|Improved Grab! (bite),;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a>)|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>|+0!(-2 size, +3 base, -1 Dex);+9!(bite);+0/--!(-2 size, +3 base, -1 Dex);-1|+10!+4 size, +4 Con, +2 natural;+8!+4 base, +4 Con;+3!+4 base, -1 Dex;+0!+1 base, -1 Wis|An eryops is a 20ft-long amphibian that lurks half-buried in shallow waters, waiting for prey to travel past. It lunges up to swallow prey and then retreats to deeper waters to digest its meal. It does not normally stay to fight if attacked, instead preferring to simply swallow its prey and then retreat.|<b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>:</b> Creatures up to two sizes smaller; +10 bludgeoning damage and +2 acid damage per round; gizzard Toughness save +3; an eryops' gizzard can hold 2 Medium, 8 Small, 32 Tiny, or 128 Diminutive or smaller opponents.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Due to its ability to change colours to match its surroundings, an eryops has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks.|
Elasmosaurus|10th|Animal||Huge|20ft., swim 50 ft.|Str +8, Dex +2, Con +6, Int -4, Wis +1, Cha -1|Notice!+14!13 ranks, +1 Wis;Stealth!-6*!0 ranks, +2 Dex, -8 size);Swim!+16!0 ranks, +8 Str, +8 bonus|Dodge Focus!,;Great Fortitude!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Tough! (x2)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+7!(-2 size, +7 base, +2 Dex);+14!(bite);+7/--!(-2 size, +7 base, +2 Dex);+2|+13!+4 size, +6 Con, +1 natural,+2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+15!+7 base, +6 Con, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Great%20Fortitude">Great Fortitude</a>;+9!+7 base, +2 Dex;+4!+3 base, +1 Wis|</p><p>Though it resides primarily in the water, an elasmosaurus only breathes air. An elasmosaurus has a total length of some 30 feet, including a tail half as long as its entire body, and weighs about 5,000 pounds. Observers who see only its head or tail might easily mistake it for a massive snake.</p><p>An elasmosaurus is aggressive and attacks anything it notices. The creature is strong, fast, and highly maneuverable, able to turn quickly and lunge at prey.|<b>Skills:</b> An elasmosaurus has a +8 racial bonus on any  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> check to perform some special action or avoid a hazard. It can always choose to take 10 on a  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> check, even if distracted or endangered. It can use the run action while swimming, provided it swims in a straight line.</p><p>*An elasmosaurus has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks in water.|
Gastonia|11th|Animal||Large|25 ft.|Str +4, Dex -1, Con +3, Int -5, Wis -1, Cha +0|Notice!+18!15 ranks, -1 Wis, +4 bonus|Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Tough! (x4)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, Scything Armour|+6!(-1 size, +8 base, -1 Dex);+12!(tail blades);+6/--!(-1 size, +8 base, -1 Dex);-1|+16!+2 size, +3 Con, +7 natural, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+10!+7 base, +3 Con;+6!+7 base, -1 Dex;+2!+3 base, -1 Wis|A gastonia is a low-slung, armoured beast similar to an ankylosaurus, but smaller, being 15 feet long and weighing about 9,000 pounds. It is heavily armoured with thick bony plates and further protected by bladed spikes that rise up around its shoulder and all down the length of the creature, including its tail. Gastonias are plant-eaters and normally peaceful but they will challenge any Medium-size or larger creature that approaches.|<b>Skills:</b> A gastonia has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.</p><p><b>Scything Armour:</b> A gastonia is covered with bladed spikes that act in concert to slice at neighboring creatures. Any creature making a melee attack against a gastonia must make a DC 19 Reflex Save or suffer +6 damage (the save DC is Str-based). On a successful save, the attacking creature takes no damage. The gastonia does not need to be aware of its attacker for this ability to take effect.|
Gecko, Giant|1st|Animal||Medium|40 ft., climb 40 ft.|Str +1, Dex +2, Con +1, Int -5, Wis +2, Cha -2|Acrobatics!+10!0 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus;Climb!+22!4 ranks, +1 Str, +8 bonus, +8 Expert Climber;Notice!+2!0 ranks, +2 Wis|Improved Initiative!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>|Expert Climber, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+2!(+0 base, +2 Dex);+3!(bite);12/--!(+0 base, +2 Dex);+6!(+2 Dex, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Initiative">Improved Initiative</a>)|+1!+1 Con;+3!+2 base, +1 Con;+4!+2 base, +2 Dex;+2!+0 base, +2 Wis|Giant geckos are agressive predators with a strong territorial streak. They will rush to attack anything up to Large size that enters their hunting grounds, taking full advantage of their spectacular climbing ability.|<b>Expert Climber:</b> The unique physiology of gecko feet allows geckos to climb any surface, no matter how slick or sheer. This ability provides them with an additional +8 bonus to Climb checks, which stacks with their racial bonus.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A giant gecko has a +8 racial  bonus on Balance and Climb checks. It can always choose to take 10 on Climb checks, even if rushed or threatened.|
Glowing Frog|2nd|Supernatural Beast||Tiny|10 ft., swim 20 ft.|Str -4, Dex +4, Con +0, Int +1, Wis +3, Cha +2|Concentration!+5!+5 base, +0 Con;Notice!+8!+5 base, +3 Wis;Stealth!+17!+5 base, +4 Dex, +8 size|!<a href="Powers.php">Powers</a> (<a href="Powers.php?Name=Heart%20Shaping">Heart Shaping</a>, <a href="Powers.php?Name=Light%20Shaping">Light Shaping</a>),;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>|Glow|+7!(+1 base, +4 Dex, +2 size);-4!(+0 base, -4 Str);17/--!(+1 base, +4 Dex, +2 size);+5|-2!+0 Con, -2 size;+3!+3 base, +0 Con;+7!+3 base, +4 Dex;+3!+0 base, +3 Wis|The glowing frog is a mysterious and revered creature found in swamps and ponds throughout the tropical islands. Though small, their supernatural powers make them potent forces. Glowing frogs often partner with nature spirits to help keep areas clear of unnatural or unwanted visitors.|<b>Glow:</b> A glowing frog emanates various colors from its body, usually as a means of attracting mates, but it can intensify the glow as a standard action sufficient to generate heat. This heat inflicts +2 fire damage on all creatures within 30 feet, unless they succeed on a Difficulty 11 Fortitude save. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.|
Hopping Vampire|6th|Undead||Medium|20ft.|Str +3, Dex +1, Con --, Int -2, Wis -1, Cha +1|Jump!+14!0 ranks, +3 Str, +8 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>;Notice!+8!9 ranks, -1 Wis|Attack Focus! (claw),;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Jump">Jump</a>),;Tough! (x2)|Curse of Vampirism, Breath Sense, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Damage%20Reduction">Damage Reduction</a> +2/magic, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Resistance%20to%20Energy">Resistance to</a> cold and electricity +2, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Supernatural%20Resistance">Supernatural Resistance</a> 15|+5!(+3 base, +1 Dex, +1 Attack Focus);+4!(claw);+1/--!(+3 base, +1 Dex);+1|+5!+3 natural armor, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+2!+2 base;+3!+2 base, +1 Dex;+4!+5 base, -1 Wis|A stiffened corpse with its arms held out in front of it, a hopping vampire is a deadly foe, despite its somewhat comical appearance. Because of the rigidity of the dead body, a hopping vampire can only move about by making short hops, but it can move with deceptive speed and agility when it sense prey nearby.|<b>Breath Sense:</b> Hopping vampires cannot see living things, and only detect them by the scent of their breath. This gives hopping vampires the <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Blindsight">blindsight</a> trait (with a range of 120 feet), but stalwart folks can hold their breath to avoid being noticed by a nearby hopping vampire. Noise also attracts them, and they may make unseeing attacks (as though the target had <a href="CombatModifiers.php?Name=Concealment">concealment</a>) if they think prey is nearby.</p><p><b>Curse of Vampirism:</b> Anyone suffering a <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Wounded">wounded</a> result from a Hopping Vampire's claw attack must succeed at a Fortitude Save (DC 13) or contract a curse that turns her into a hopping vampire herself. This is hard to counteract, but determined folks usually find a way. Sticky rice, abstaining from anything fun, constant dancing about and the consultations of learned scholars are almost always involved. If no assistance is found, the victim dies in 12 hours and rises as a hopping vampire in another 12 hours from that point.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A hopping vampire has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Jump">Jump</a> checks.|
Liopleurodon|20th|Animal||Colossal|10ft., swim 100 ft.|Str +12, Dex +2, Con +8, Int -4, Wis +2, Cha +0|Notice!+26!24 ranks, +2 Wis;Stealth!-14*!0 ranks, +2 Dex, -16 size;Swim!+20!0 ranks, +12 Str, +8 bonus|Attack Focus! (bite),;Dodge Focus!,;Great Fortitude!,;Improved Grab!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Tough! (x3)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>|+10!(-8 size, +15 base, +2 Dex, +1 Attack Focus);+21!(bite);+10/--!(-8 size, +15 base, +2 Dex, +1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Dodge%20Focus">Dodge Focus</a>);+2|+22!+8 size, +8 Con, +3 natural, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+22!+12 base, +8 Con, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Great%20Fortitude">Great Fortitude</a>;+14!+12 base, +2 Dex;+8!+6 base, +2 Wis|A liopluerodon is an immense aquatic predator, 80 feet in length and weighing easily 300,000 pounds. These gigantic creatures sail through warm shallow seas, eating anything and everything that comes within range. For all their size they are capable of swift movement. They fear nothing and any attack that does manage to damage them is only likely to stir up their rage. They are known to attack ships, and areas that liopleurodon have claimed as their hunting grounds are avoided by all captains.|<b>Skills:</b> A liopluerodon has a +8 racial bonus on any  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> check to perform some special action or avoid a hazard. It can always choose to take 10 on a  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> check, even if distracted or endangered. It can use the run action while swimming, provided it swims in a straight line.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>:</b> Creatures up to two sizes smaller; +17 bludgeoning damage and +8 acid damage per round; gizzard Toughness save +9; a liopluerodon's gizzard can hold 2 Large, 8 Medium, 32 Small, or 128 Tiny or smaller opponents.</p><p>*A liopluerodon has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks in water.|
Manticore Cactus|6th|Plant||Large|0 ft.|Str -2, Dex +1, Con +2, Int --, Wis -2, Cha -4|||Paralysis, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Ability%20Score%20Loss">Ability Drain</a>, Water Sight|+4!(+4 base, +1 Dex, -1 size) or <b>+6</b> <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Grapple">grapple</a>;+3! ranged (and paralysis) or <b>+1</b> melee (and paralysis);14/--!(+4 base, +1 Dex, -1 size);+1|+8!+2 Con, +6 natural armor;+7!+5 base, +2 Con;+3!+2 base, +1 Dex;+0!+2 base, -2 Wis|Vegetable predators, manticore cactii can sense any craeture with water in its body that comes nearby. These dangerous plants lash out with the lengthy black spines to kill or paralyze their prey and soak their wide-ranging roots in moist flesh. Their needles have a range increment of 10 feet and a maximum range of 50 feet.</p><p>Manticore cactii grow in arid regions, usually along game trails where a source of watery prey is abundant. Characters can recognize such a plant with a Difficulty 20 <a href="Skills.php?Name=Survival">Survival</a> check or a Difficulty 25 <a href="Skills.php?Name=Knowledge">Knowledge</a> (local) check.|<b>Paralysis:</b> In addition to taking regular damage, a target hit by a manticore cactus' flung needles must make a Difficulty 15 Fortitude save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Paralyzed">paralyzed</a> for 1 minute. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.</p><p><b>Ability Drain:</b> A manticore cactus within 30 feet of a helpless creature can make a +6 <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Grapple">grapple</a> (with an additional +4 since the target is probably <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Prone">prone</a>) attempt against that creature. On a successful check the victim takes +2 damage as the cactus' root extrude long needles and sink them into the victim's flesh. Every following round, the victim takes 1 point of Constitution damage as the cactus drains water and nutrients from the hapless creature. The cactus may make a <a href="CombatDamage.php#Recovery">recovery check</a> as a free action for every point of Constitution thus drained.</p><p><b>Water Sight:</b> Manticore cactii are incredibly sensitive to moisture nearby, allowing them to automatically detect the presence of water -- and in effect most living creatures -- within 100 feet. Drenching the plant in water (requiring at least a gallon of water) effectively blinds it until the water evaporates.|
Mechanithrall|5th|Necrotech Construct||Medium|30 ft.|Str +3, Dex +1, Con --, Int -2, Wis +0, Cha -2|Climb!+6!3 ranks, +3 Str;Notice!+3!3 ranks, +0 Wis;Stealth!+4!3 ranks, +1 Dex|Improved Initiative!,;Lightning Reflexes!|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> 60 ft., Steamslam|+4!(+3 base, +1 Dex);+7!(slam);+4/+6!(+3 base, +1 Dex/+3 Str);+5|+4!+4 natural armor;+1!+1 base, +0 Con;+2!+1 base, +1 Dex;+4!+4 base, +0 Wis|These terrible creations hiss and clank and whirr as their necromechanical engines drive them forward. Hideous corpses given animation through both magic and bizarre mechanics, they appear as a hybrid of dead flesh, gears and bolts, mechanical joints grinding as they move. Their immense fists are charged with steam-powered fury.|<b>Steamslam:</b> A mechanithrall can use the steam building up in its mechanical fittings to deliver a powerful punch to its opponent. This sudden extension of its forearm attacks with an additional +4 attack bonus and does an extra +3 damage on top of the normal punch attack. After making a steamslam attack, a mechanithrall takes a level of <a href="CombatDamage.php">non-lethal damage</a>. A mechanithrall that falls <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Unconscious">unconscious</a> simply stands perfectly still, unable to take actions. As it has no Constitution score and cannot succeed on Recovery checks, an unconscious mechanthrall remains unconscious until ten hours have passed, at which point its engine has built up enough pressure for the construct to begin operating again, and it immediately awakens with all non-lethal damage removed.|
Megaraptor|8th|Animal||Huge|60 ft.|Str +5, Dex +2, Con +5, Int -4, Wis +2, Cha +0|Jump!+25!11 ranks, +5 Str, +8 bonus, +2 speed;Notice!+10!0 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus;Stealth!+2!0 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus, -8 size;Survival!+10!0 ranks, +2 Wis, +8 bonus|Double Strike!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Run!,;Tough!,;Track!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Pounce">Pounce</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+6!(-2 size, +6 base, +2 Dex);+11!(talons) or <b>+6</b> (foreclaws) or <b>+9</b> (bite);+6/--!(-2 size, +6 base, +2 Dex);+2|+13!+4 size, +5 Con, +3 natural,+1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+11!+6 base, +5 Con;+8!+6 base, +2 Dex;+4!+2 base, +2 Wis|</p><p>This creature is a larger version of the <a href="Creatures.php?Name=Deinonychus">deinonychus</a>, standing about 12 feet tall with a total length of 24 feet. It has the same appearance, habits and abilities of the smaller version.|<b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Pounce">Pounce</a>:</b> If a megaraptor charges, it can attack a single target with both its talons and its bite in a single round.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A megaraptor has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Jump">Jump</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Survival">Survival</a> checks.|
Mosquito, Giant|2nd|Vermin||Small|10 ft., fly 50 ft. (average)|Str +0, Dex +4, Con +1, Int --, Wis +0, Cha -3|Notice!+4!0 ranks, +4 bonus|!--|Attach, Blood Drain, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> (60 ft.), <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Disease">Disease</a>|+6!(+1 size, +4 Dex);+1!(bite, plus blood drain);+6/--!(+1 size, +4 Dex);+4|+1!+1 Con;+3!+2 base, +1 Con;+4!+2 base, +2 Dex;+0!+0 base, +0 Wis|</p><p>Giant mosquitoes are nearly a yard long. They are mostly found in swampy areas, and other places with stagnant water.|<b>Attach:</b> If a giant mosquito hits with a bite attack, it latches onto the opponent's body. An attached mosquito is effectively <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Grappled">grappling</a> its prey. The giant mosquito is unable to use its <a href="Combat.php#Dodge">Dodge</a>, but holds on with great tenacity. Giant mosquitoes have a +12 racial bonus on <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Grapple">grapple</a> checks. An attached mosquito can be struck with a weapon or grappled itself. To remove an attached mosquito through grappling, the opponent must achieve a pin against the mosquito.</p><p><b>Blood Drain:</b> An attached giant mosquito drains blood, dealing 1 point of Constitution damage each round it begins its turn attached to a victim. Once it has dealt 2 points of Constitution damage, it detaches and flies off to digest the meal. If its victim dies before the mosquito's appetite has been sated, the mosquito detaches and seeks new prey.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Disease">Disease</a>:</b> There is 10% chance (19-20 on a d20) that any given giant mosquito is carrying a disease of some variety. Anyone bitten by a disease-carrying giant mosquito has a chance of contracting the disease.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A giant mosquito has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.|
Ndalawo|10th|Undead|Incorporeal|Medium|40 ft., fly 60ft.|Str --, Dex +6, Con --, Int -3, Wis +2, Cha -2|Notice!+23!13 ranks, +2 Wis, +8 bonus;Stealth!+14!0 ranks, +6 Dex, +8 bonus|Dodge Focus! (x2),;Double Strike!,;Move-by Action|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Ability%20Score%20Loss">Ability Damage</a>, Create Spawn, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> to 60 feet, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Pounce">Pounce</a>|+11!(+5 base, +6 Dex) or (<b>+9</b> bite and <b>+9</b> claw);+1!(claw) or <b>+2 Str</b> (bite);23/--!(+5 base, +6 Dex, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Dodge%20Focus">Dodge Focus</a>);+6|+0!+0 base, - Con;--;+9!+3 base, +6 Dex;+9!+7 base, +2 Wis|Also known as the shadow leopard, the ndalawo is a leopard that has been transformed into an undead shadow.|<b>Ability Damage:</b> Any living creature struck by the ndalawo's claws suffers 1 point of Str damage, and any living creature struck by its bite suffers 2 points of Str damage. Any creature killed by the ndalawo becomes a shadow under its control.</p><p><b>Create Spawn:</b> Any creature killed by a ndalawo becomes a <a href="CreaturesTemplates?Name=Ghost">ghost</a> under the ndalawo's control three rounds after its death.|
Onijegi|1st|Monstrous Humanoid|Aquatic|Medium|5 ft., swim 50 ft.|Str +0, Dex +1, Con +1, Int +0, Wis +0, Cha +1|Notice!+4!0 ranks, +0 Wis, +4 bonus;Swim!+8!0 ranks, +0 Str, +8 bonus|Exotic Weapon Training! (<a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Net">net</a>)|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> out to 60 feet.|+2!+1 base, +1 Dex;+3! (<a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Spear">spear</a>);12/11!(+1 base, +1 Dex/+1 base, +0 Str);+1|+1!+1 Con;+1!+0 base, +1 Con;+3!+2 base, +1 Dex;+2!+2 base, +0 Wis|Onijegi are merfolk; beautiful humans from the waist up, and long scaly tails below. They are usually dark-skinned with green and blue highlights in their hair, and the bright colours of tropical fish in their scales. The adorn themselves with coral and shells. Groups of onijegi can be found sunning themselves on exposed rocks, telling stories of their hunts and the intrigues among their undersea nations. They are usually friendly and talkative, but can be dangerous if for some reason they feel threatened or otherwise suspicious.|Onijegi may advance in any of the <a href="Roles.php">heroic roles</a>.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Onijegi receive a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks. Onijegi also receive a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks. Onijegi may always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. An onijegi can use a <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Move%20All%20Out">move all out</a> action when swimming, provided it travels in a straight line.|
Pachycephalosaurus|13th|Animal||Huge|60 ft.|Str +8, Dex +2, Con +4, Int -5, Wis +2, Cha -1|Notice!+24!17 ranks, +2 Wis +2 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>|Great Fortitude!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>),;Tough! (x3)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Powerful%20Charge">Powerful Charge</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+9!(-2 size, +9 base, +2 Dex);+13!(headbutt);+9/--!(-2 size, +9 base, +2 Dex);+2|+12!+4 size, +4 Con, +1 natural, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+14!+8 base, +4 Con, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Great%20Fortitude">Great Fortitude</a>;+10!+8 base, +2 Dex;+6!+4 base, +2 Wis|A pachycephalosaurus has a body about 25 feet long and weighs about 15,000 pounds. It stands on two legs and is characterized by a massive bare skull of solid bone that it uses as a powerful battering ram. These creatures travel in large herds and will defend their young against any intruders of Large size or greater. Smaller creatures will be ignored unless they attack or otherwise threaten the herd, at which point the strongest members will begin charging one after the other until the threat is gone.|<b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Powerful%20Charge">Powerful Charge</a>:</b> When a pachycephalosaurus charges, its headbutt attack deals +18 damage.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A pachycephalosaurus has a +2 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.|
Parasaurolophus|15th|Animal||Gargantuan|30 ft.|Str +8, Dex +1, Con +3, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -1|Notice!+23!18 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>|Great Fortitude!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>),;Tough! (x4)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Trample">Trample</a>|+8!(-4 size, +11 base, +1 Dex);+4!(bite);+8/--!(-4 size, +11 base, +1 Dex);+1|+14!+6 size, +3 Con, +1 natural, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+14!+9 base, +3 Con, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Great%20Fortitude">Great Fortitude</a>;+10!+9 base, +1 Dex;+6!+5 base, +1 Wis|A parasaurolophus is a non-agressive herbivore that will almost always choose to run from any danger. Its only attack, a weak bite, is unlikely to deter predators, and it will only <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Trample">Trample</a> other creatures accidentally.</p><p>These creatures are 35 feet long and weigh in excess of 25,000 pounds. Despite their inoffensive nature, they can be very dangerous because of their tendencies to form immense herds and to run from danger. Being caught in front of a stampeding herd of these animals can be as dangerous as any attack from a more ferocious dinosaur.|<b>Skills:</b> A parasaurolophus has a +4 bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.</p><p><b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Trample">Trample</a>:</b> Damage +12, Reflex Save DC 23 for half damage. The save difficulty is Strength-based.|
Pteranodon|8th|Animal||Huge|15 ft., fly 50ft. (poor)|Str +2, Dex +2, Con +1, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -1|Notice!+19!11 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>|Dodge Focus!,!Move-by Action!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+6!(-2 size, +6 base, +2 Dex);+5!(bite);+7/--!(-2 size, +6 base, +2 Dex, +1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Dodge%20Focus">Dodge Focus</a>);+2|+5!+4 size, +1 Con;+7!+6 base, +1 Con;+8!+6 base, +2 Dex;+3!+2 base, +1 Wis|A pteranodon is a soaring fish-eater that is not above scavenging any creature that looks big enough to form a meal and small enough to not be much of a threat. They nest in vast clifftop rookeries overlooking the oceans where they hunt, and any intrusion into their nesting grounds will be met with shrieks and diving attacks from all sides.</p><p>Pteranodons have a wingspan of 30 feet, but only weighs 100 pounds. Their light construction means that they can only carry a <a href="PlayingPhysical.php#Carrying">Medium Load</a> for their strength (116 pounds).|<b>Skills:</b> A pteranodon has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.|
Quetzalcoatlus|14th|Animal||Gargantuan|10 ft., fly 40ft. (poor)|Str +6, Dex +1, Con +2, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -1|Notice!+25!17 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>|Dodge Focus!,;Move-by Action!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>),;Snatch!,;Tough| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+7!(-4 size, +10 base, +1 Dex);+8!(bite);18/--!(-4 size, +10 base, +1 Dex, +1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Dodge%20Focus">Dodge Focus</a>);+1|+9!+6 size, +2 Con,+1 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+11!+9 base, +2 Con;+10!+9 base, +1 Dex;+5!+4 base, +1 Wis|A quetzalcoatlus is an immense aerial scavenger that soars high to find the huge corpses of dinosaurs far below. Enormous beyond belief, these creatures will vigourously defend their meals, or even attack to drive off smaller animals. Lingering near a dead dinosaur can often mean a sudden attack from above.</p><p>Quetzalcoatli have a wingspan of 50 feet, and weigh 300 pounds. Their light construction means that they can only carry a <a href="PlayingPhysical.php#Carrying">Medium Load</a> for their strength (346 pounds).|<b>Skills:</b> A quetzalcoatlus has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.|
Rat|1st|Animal||Tiny|15 ft., climb 15 ft., swim 15 ft.|Str -4, Dex +2, Con +0, Int -4, Wis +1, Cha -4|Acrobatics!+10!0 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus;Climb!+12!2 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus;Stealth!+16!2 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus, +4 size;Swim!+10!0 ranks, +2 Dex, +8 bonus|Evasion!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+4!(+2 Dex, +2 size);-4!(unarmed);14/--!(+2 Dex, +2 size);+2|-2!0 Con, -2 size;+2!+2 base;+4!+2 base, +2 Dex;+1!+0 base, +1 Wis|Found nearly everywhere, rats are not particularly dangerous animals, but gathered in swarms they can overwhelm unsuspecting foes.|<b>Skills:</b> Rats have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks, and a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Acrobatics">Acrobatics</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a>, and  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks. A rat can always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. A rat uses its Dexterity modifier instead of its Strength modifier for <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> and  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks. A rat has a +8 racial bonus on any  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> check to perform some special action or avoid a hazard. It can always choose to take 10 on a  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> check, even if distracted or endangered. It can use the run action while swimming, provided it swims in a straight line.|
Rat, Dire|1st|Animal||Small|40 ft., climb 20 ft.|Str +0, Dex +3, Con +1, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -3|Climb!+11!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus;Notice!+4!3 ranks, +1 Wis;Stealth!+8!1 rank, +3 Dex, +4 size;Swim!+11!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus|Evasion!,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Disease">Disease</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+4!(+3 Dex, +1 size);+0!(bite);+4/--!(+3 Dex, +1 size);+2|+0!+1 Con, -1 size;+3!+2 base, +1 Con;+5!+2 base, +3 Dex;+1!+0 base, +1 Wis|Dire rats are hideous rodents up to 4 feet long.|<b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Disease">Disease</a>:</b> There is 10% chance (19-20 on a d20) that any given dire rat is carrying a disease of some variety. Anyone bitten by a disease-carrying dire rat has a chance of contracting the disease.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Dire rats have a +8 bonus on  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks. Dire rats have a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks and can always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. Dire rats use their Dexterity modifier for <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> and  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks.</p><p>Anyone bitten by a dire rat must make a Fortitude save (Difficulty 13) to avoid being infected with a disease doing 1 point of Constitution damage.|
Reliquary Guardian|7th|Construct||Tiny|20 ft.|Str +3, Dex +5, Con --, Int --, Wis +3, Cha +1||Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Damage%20Reduction">Damage Reduction</a> +3/supernatural, Magic Tracking, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Supernatural%20Resistance">Supernatural Resistance</a> 13|+12!+5 base, +5 Dex, +2 size;+4!(spear plus poison);22/20!(+5 base, +5 Dex, +2 size/+5 base, +3 Str, +2 size);+5|+1!+0 Con, -2 size, +3 natural armor;+2!+2 base, +0 Con;+7!+2 base, +5 Dex;+5!+2 base, +3 Wis|Reliquary guardians are magical constructs created to protect the remains of honoured ancestors. They are harmless statuettes until placed upon a container holding the remains of a dead human being.</p><p>Once that happens, the construct becomes active. It will animate and attack anyone that approaches within 5 feet of the container unless that person is a direct descendant of the person whose body it guards. The guardian can magically detect the proper bloodline, and it cannot be fooled. Note that while the guardian will nto attack direct descendants, it is not under their control, either. If a direct descendant removes the reliquary guardian from its resting place, it becomes inactive until reset.|<b>Magic Tracking:</b> A reliquary guardian can sense the exact location of the remains and grave items it is tasked to guard from any distance. If the remains or any grave items are stolen, it can track the missing objects perfectly over any distance.</p><p><b>Poison:</b> The reliquary guardian's spear is tipped with poison. Any creature that suffers damage from the spear must succeed on a Difficulty 13 Fortitude save or suffer 2 points of Strength damage. After 1 minute, the victim must make another Fortitude save or suffer an additional 2 points of Strength damage.|
Sea Drake|12th|Supernatural Beast|Aquatic|Huge|20 ft., swim 60 ft.|Str +9, Dex +2, Con +6, Int -4, Wis +1, Cha +2|Notice!+9!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +8 bonus;Swim!+17!0 ranks, +9 Str, +8 bonus|Attack Focus! (bite),;All-out Attack!,;Improved Initiative!,;!<a href="Powers.php">Power</a> (<a href="Powers.php?Name=Water%20Shaping">Water Shaping</a>),;Snatch|Bellow, Hurricane Breath, Ink Cloud|+12!(+12 base, +2 Dex, -2 size) (<b>+13</b> bite);+14!(bite), <b>+10</b> (claw);22/--!(+12 base, +2 Dex, -2 size);+6!(+2 Dex, +4 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Improved%20Initiative">Improved Initiative</a>)|+16!+6 Con, +4 size, +6 natural armor;+14!+8 base, +6 Con;+10!+8 base, +2 Dex;+5!+4 base, +1 Wis|Bane to ship captains everywhere, sea drakes are agressive and territorial creatures with a fondness for attacking passing ships. They are long, serpentine reptiles with fearsome webbed claws.</p><p>Their ability to unleash a blast of tornado-strength wind can easily blow an entire crew from their vessel or even scuttle smaller ships. A sea drake seeking to escape can unleash a cloud of foul-smelling ink to conceal its retreat.|<b>Bellow:</b> A sea drake can release a horrible roar. Anyone caught within the 40-foot cone of this effect must make a Difficulty 22 Reflex save or be knocked back 5 feet and take +2 damage. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.</p><p><b>Hurricane Breath:</b> Three times per day a sea drake can unleash a breath of incredibly violent wind. Treat this as a use of the <a href="Powers.php?Name=Wind%20Shaping">Wind Shaping</a> power that emanates from the sea drake's direction and alsts until its next turn. This is a blast of hurricane-force wind. Creatures of Medium size or smaller must make a Difficulty 22 Fortitude save or be blown away. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based. A creature blown away is knocked prone and rolls away from the sea drake 20 feet + 1 foot for every 1 point by which the creature failed its Fortitude save. The creature takes +1 damage for every 10 feet it is blown back.</p><p><b>Ink Cloud:</b> A sea drake can emit a spherical cloud of jet-black ink with a radius of 100 feet once per day. This cloud is completely impenetrable to any sort of vision, including <a href="Feats.php?Name=Night%20Vision">Night Vision</a>. This ability has no effect outside wataer.</p><p><b>Water Shaping:</b> A sea drake can use the <a href="Powers.php?Name=Water%20Shaping">Water Shaping</a> power as though it had power ranks equal to its level.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Sea drakes have a +8 racial bonus on Notice and Swim checks. A sea drake can always choose to take 10 on a Swim check, even if rushed or threatened. A sea drake can use the run action while swimming but only if it moves in a straight line.|
Shark|3rd|Animal||Medium|swim 60 ft.|Str +1, Dex +2, Con +1, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -4|Notice!+7!6 ranks, +1 Wis;Swim!+9!0 ranks, +1 Str, +8 bonus|Tough! (x3)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Blindsense">Blindsense</a>, Keen Scent|+4!(+2 Dex);+3!(bite);14/--!(+2 Dex);+2|+4!+1 Con, +3 Tough;+4!+3 base, +1 Con;+5!+3 base, +2 Dex;+2!+1 base, +1 Wis|Sharks are aggressive, carnivorous, fish liable to make unprovoked attacks against anything approaching them. Medium sharks are from 5 to 8 feet long and not usually dangerous to creatures other than their prey (smaller fish and sea mammals).|<b>Keen Scent:</b> A shark can notice creatures by scent in a 180-foot radius and detect blood in the water at ranges of up to a mile.|
Siren|7th|Monstrous Humanoid|Aquatic|Medium|30 ft., swim 50 ft.|Str +1, Dex +1, Con +1, Int +1, Wis +2, Cha +4|Bluff!+18!10 ranks, +4 Cha, +4 bonus;Disguise!+18*!10 ranks, +4 Cha, +4 bonus;Perform!(singing) +17!10 ranks, +4 Cha, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>;Swim!+9!0 ranks, +1 Str, +8 bonus|Ability Focus! (song of longing),;!<a href="Powers.php">Power</a> (<a href="Powers.php?Name=Psychic%20Blast">Psychic Blast</a>),;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Perform">Perform</a>)|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Alternate%20Form">Alternate Form</a>, Paralyzing Beauty, Song of Longing|+8!(+7 base +1 Dex);+2!(+1 <a href="EquipmentWeapons.php?Name=Knife/Dagger">dagger</a>, +1 Str);18/18!(+7 base, +1 Dex/+7 base, +1 Str);+1|+1!+1 Con;+3!+2 base, +1 Con;+6!+5 base, +1 Dex;+7!+5 base, +2 Wis|Cousins to the <a href="Creatures.php?Name=Onijegi">onijegi</a> but far more cruel and mischevious, sirens resemble beautiful women from the waist up, and like their cousins, shimmering scaly fish from the waist down. But unlike the <a href="Creatures.php?Name=Onijegi">onijegi</a>, sirens can shift into a fully human appearance, and do so to lure unsuspecting men to them for reproduction and, usually, death.</p><p>Their primary weapon for drawing men to them is their unearthly song, which is so seductive to men that it will drive them to leap into the sea, attempting to reach the source of that beauty. Entire ships have been depopulated by these crooning creatures, who then rescue the lucky individuals they would mate with, while leaving their fellows to drown. Once the human males have served their purpose, they are usually drowned as well, if they have not been driven mad by the unending hypnotism of their new loves.|<b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Alternate%20Form">Alternate Form</a>:</b> A siren may assume a fully human form as a standard action at will, or return to its natural form likewise. The human form it takes is always the same, and resembles the siren's natural form from the waist up, so the siren can be recognized in either form.</p><p><b>Paralyzing Beauty:</b> This ability operates continuously, affecting all humans who find women attractive within 60 feet of the siren. Those who gaze directly at the siren must succeed on a Difficulty 17 Fortitude save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Paralyzed">paralyzed</a> for three rounds. The siren can suppress or resume this ability as a free action. The save Difficulty is Charisma-based.</p><p><b>Song of Longing:</b> The song of a siren calls to something deep in the heart of everyone who hears it. Those attracted to women within 300 feet of a singing siren must make a Difficulty 19 Will save every two rounds or make every attempt (ignoring their own personal safety) to reach the siren. Those attracted to men must make a single Difficulty 19 Will save upon first hearing the siren's song or become incapacitated by helpless weeping (same effect as <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Fascinated">fascinated</a>) until the song ends.</p><p><b>Psychic Blast:</b> A siren may use the supernatural <a href="Powers.php">power</a> <a href="Powers.php?Name=Psychic%20Blast">Psychic Blast</a> as though possessing power ranks equal to her level.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A siren receives a +4 racial bonus to <a href="Skills.php?Name=Bluff">Bluff</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Disguise">Disguise</a> checks. In addition, a siren receives a +8 racial bonus to <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks. A siren can always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. A siren can use the <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Move%20All%20Out">move all out</a> action when swimming, but only when travelling in a straight line.|
