 its bite attack drains blood for 1 point of Constitution damage each round it remains attached. If the bite attack hit but did no damage, the smilodon cannot drain the opponent's blood but remains attached until it is removed or decides to let go.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Pounce">Pounce</a>:</b> If a smilodon charges, it can attack a single target with both its claws and its bite in a single round.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A smilodon has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks.</p><p>*In areas of tall grass or heavy undergrowth, the <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> bonus improves to +8.|
Snake, Constrictor|3rd|Animal||Medium|20 ft., climb 20 ft.|Str +3, Dex +3, Con +1, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -4|Climb!+14!3 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus;Notice!+5!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus;Stealth!+10!3 ranks, +3 Dex, +4 bonus;Swim!+11!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus|Tough! (x2),;Improved Grab| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Constrict">Constrict</a>|+3!(+3 Dex);+3!(bite or constriction);+3/--!(+3 Dex);+3|+3!+1 Con, +2 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+4!+3 base +1 Con;+6!+3 base, +3 Dex;+2!+1 base, +1 Wis|Constrictor snakes usually are not aggressive and flee when confronted. They hunt for food but do not attempt to make a meal out of any creature too large to constrict. Constrictor snakes hunt by grabbing prey with their mouths and then squeezing it with their powerful bodies.|<b>Skills:</b> Snakes have a +4 bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks. A snake can always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. A snake uses its Dexterity modifier instead of its Strength modifier for <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> and  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks.|
Snake, Viper|1st|Animal||Tiny|15 ft., climb 15 ft., swim 15 ft.|Str -3, Dex +3, Con +0, Int -5, Wis +1, Cha -4|Climb!+11!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus;Notice!+9!4 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus;Stealth!+15!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +4 bonus, +8 size;Swim!+11!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus|Attack Focus! (bite)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>|+6!(+1 Attack Focus, +3 Dex, +2 size);-5!(bite, plus poison);+5/--!(+3 Dex, +2 size);+3|-2!+0 Con, -2 size;+2!+2 base, +0 Con;+5!+2 base, +3 Dex;+1!+0 base, +1 Wis|Vipers are not particularly aggressive, but will often lash out with a bite attack before attempting to retreat. They rely on their venomous bite to kill prey and to defend themselves.|<b><a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>:</b> A viper's bite requires a Difficulty 10 Fortitude saving throw. The venom deals initial and secondary damage of 2 Constitution</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Snakes have a +4 bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks. A snake can always choose to take 10 on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. A snake uses its Dexterity modifier instead of its Strength modifier for <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a> and  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks. Vipers have a +8 bonus on  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks and can always choose to take 10 on  <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks, even while threatened.|
Spinosaurus|20th|Animal||Gargantuan|20 ft.|Str +12, Dex +1, Con +7, Int -4, Wis +1, Cha +0|Notice!+29!23 ranks, +1 Wis, +2 bonus, +3 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Skill%20Focus">Skill Focus</a>|Attack Focus! (bite),;Improved Grab!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>),;Tough! (x5)| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Scent">Scent</a>, Shake, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>|+12!(-4 size, +15 base, +1 Dex) (<b>+13</b> with bite);+18!(bite);+12/--!(-4 size, +15 base, +1 Dex);+1|+18!+4 size, +7 Con, +2 natural, +5 <a href="Feats.php?Name=Tough">Tough</a>;+18!+11 base, +7 Con;+12!+11 base, +1 Dex;+8!+6 base, +2 Wis|The spinosaurus is one of the most massive predators on land; more than 50 feet long and weighing over ten tons. The tall sail on its back only increases the terrifying impact of this creature. Fortunately, it is not as swift as some other large predators and is generally a scavenger rather than an active hunter.|<b>Shake:</b> If a spinosaurus successfully starts a <a href="CombatActions.php?Name=Grapple">grapple</a> with its bite attack, it deals automatic bite damage each round it maintains the hold as it shakes its prey violently in its jaws. The spinosaurus can deal this damage even if moving or pinning its opponent.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Swallow%20Whole">Swallow Whole</a>:</b> Creatures up to three sizes smaller; +18 bludgeoning damage and +7 acid damage per round; gizzard Toughness save +13; a spinosaurus' gizzard can hold 2 Medium, 8 Small, 32 Tiny, or 128 Diminutive or smaller opponents.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> A spinosaurus has a +2 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks.|
