Swarm, Killer Bee|7th|Vermin|Swarm|Diminutive|5 ft., fly 40 ft. (good)|Str -5, Dex +4, Con +0, Int --, Wis +1, Cha -1|Notice!+5!0 ranks, +1 Wis, +4 bonus);Survival!+1!0 ranks, +1 Wis|!--| <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Darkvision">Darkvision</a> (60 ft.), Distraction, Immune to Weapon Damage, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>|<a href="CreaturesSubTypes.php?Name=Swarm">Swarm!;+4!(sting, plus poison);+13/--!(+5 base, +4 Dex, +4 size);+4|-4!0 Con, -4 size;+5!+5 base;+6!+2 base, +4 Dex;+3!+2 base, +1 Wis|Killer bees are named for their extremely aggressive nature, and their habit of swarming anything they feel is threatening their hive. Killer bees have a strong aversion to the color black, and will attack anything of that color that approaches within 30 ft. of their hive.|<b>Distraction:</b> Any living creature that begins its turn within a killer bee swarm must succeed on a Difficulty 13 Fortitude save or be nauseated for 1 round. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.</p><p><b> <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Poison">Poison</a>:</b> Injury, Fortitude Difficulty 13, initial and secondary damage 1 Con. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Killer bees have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> checks. They also have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Survival">Survival</a> checks to orient themselves.</p>|
Swarm, Razorbats|7th|Animal|Swarm|Tiny|fly 30ft. (good)|Str -2, Dex +3, Con +0, Int -4, Wis +0, Cha +0|Notice!+8!0 ranks, +0 Wis, +8 bonus;Stealth!+11!0 ranks, +3 Dex, +8 bonus|Ability Focus! (distraction),;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a>),;Skill Focus! (<a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a>)|<a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Blindsight">Blindsight</a>, Distraction, Repeated Attacks, Sonic Scream|<a href="CreaturesSubTypes.php?Name=Swarm">Swarm!;+6;20/--!(+5 base, +3 Dex, +2 size);+3|-4!+0 Con, -4 size;+5!+5 base, +0 Con;+8!+5 base, +3 Dex;+2!+2 base, +0 Wis|Razorbats are voracious predators that descend on their prey in huge swarms, hit it with a sonic scream to stun it, and then descend for the kill.|<b>Distraction:</b> Any living creature that begins its turn with a razorbat swarm in its square must make a Difficulty 15 Fortitude save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Nauseated">nauseated</a> for one round.</p><p><b>Sonic Scream:</b> A swarm of razorbats acting in concert can focus the tiny shrieks they use for echolocation into a cone of deadly vibration.</p><p>A razorbat swarm can emit a sonic scream once every three rounds as a standard action. The scream extends in a 30-foot cone. Creatures within the cone take +6 sonic damage and must make a Difficulty 13 Fortitude save or be <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Stunned">stunned</a> for one round and <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Deafened">deafened</a> for one hour. The save Difficulty is Constitution-based.</p><p>In addition, all non-supernatural objects of glass, crystal, ceramic or porcelain in the cone weighing less than 1 pound shatter.</p><p><b>Repeated Attacks:</b> Razorbats have claws on their wings and barbs on their tails, making them dangerous opponents. A razorbat swarm deals +2 additional damage than a normal swarm of its level.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Razorbat swarms have a +8 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Notice">Notice</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> checks.|
Tuyewara|17|Construct||Medium|20 ft. (can't run)|Str +6, Dex +1, Con --, Int -4, Wis +3, Cha -4|Climb!+10!0 ranks, +6 Str, +4 bonus;Stealth!+5!0 ranks, +1 Dex, +4 bonus;Swim!+10!0 ranks, +6 Str, +4 bonus|Night Vision!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span>,;Sneak Attack!<span class="superscript"><a href="Creatures.php#BonusFeats">B</a></span> (x3)|Death Attack, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Damage%20Reduction">Damage Reduction</a> +4/supernatural, Invisible at Night, <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Resistance%20to%20Energy">Resistance to Energy</a> +8 (acid, cold, electricity, fire and sonic), <a href="CreaturesTraits.php?Name=Supernatural%20Resistance">Supernatural Resistance</a> 20|+13!(+12 base, +1 Dex);+6!(+6 Str) or (<b>+10</b> sneak attack);23/--!(+12 base, +1 Dex);+1|+7!+1 base, +6 natural armor;+5!+5 base, +0 Con;+6!+5 base, +1 Dex;+8!+5 base, +3 Wis|The tuyewara is a gruesome construct made of corpses that is designed to be sent to assassinate the creator's enemies. It is a stitched-together mockery of the human form with no legs below the knees, and no tongue. The lack of legs prevents it from running away, and the lack of a tongue makes it unable to complain about its treatment. If forced into open combat, a tuyewara never retreats -- some say they seek their own destruction as a way of ending their tormented existence.|<b>Death Attack:</b> If the tuyewara studies its victim for 3 rounds and then makes a <a href="CombatModifiers.php?Name=Surprise%20Attack">surprise attack</a> that successfully deals at least a <a href="PlayingConditions.php?Name=Hurt">hurt</a> result, the surprise attack may slay the target outright.</p><p>While studying the victim, the tuyewara can undertake other actions so long as its attention stays focused on the target and the target does not detect the tuyewara or recognize the tuyewara as an enemy. If the victim fails a Difficulty 18 Fortitude save against the death attack, she dies. If the victim's saving throw is successful, she takes damage as a normal surprise attack.</p><p>Once the tuyewara has competed the three rounds of study, it must make the death attack within the next three rounds. If a death attack is attempted and fails (the victim makes her saving throw) or if the tuyewara does not launch the attack within three rounds of completing its study, three new rounds of study are required before it can attempt another death attack.</p><p><b>Invisible at Night:</b> From dusk until dawn, the tuyewara is rendered invisible. A successful use of the <a href="Powers.php?Name=Severance">Severance</a> power will remove the invisibility for a single round.</p><p><b>Skills:</b> Tuyewara have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="Skills.php?Name=Climb">Climb</a>, <a href="Skills.php?Name=Stealth">Stealth</a> and <a href="Skills.php?Name=Swim">Swim</a> checks.|
